I placed an order through door dash fn 9/5/2019 for two burritos and a side of guacamole, $30 including a $3.99 delivery fee. The order was prepaid on my credit card with tip and arrived with only one burrito. We contacted Door Dash expecting they would make good on this. To our surprise when Jerico contacted the restaurant, they claimed that the order was complete and would only offer a 25% refund in 5-7 days! A truly disappointing experience from both vendors. I believe the poor customer service is isolated to this store, however, I will not support either this location or DoorDash as no one would own the situation. It sucks to be working late, be made to feel like I'm LUCKY to get part of my money back and worse, have a cashier say we have nothing better to do than claim we didn't get our order. It's the principle not the money - do better!

I’ve gone to this location many times and have never had a problem with the food. However, today I ordered a steak burrito bowl. When I first opened the burrito bowl, the first thing I noticed was that it was 3/4 of the way full. A quarter of the bowl had almost no rice, beans or any other additional toppings. Another thing that I noticed was that the steak slices were not evenly cut as they were all different shapes and sizes. The guacamole was not completely mashed and I found big chunks throughout the dish. It was also not evenly seasoned because weirdly, the big chunks were incredibly salty while there were other times when the guacamole tasted completely unseasoned. Lastly, my biggest complaint was that I noticed several pieces of something hard in the bowl. These looked like some sort of seed, almost like a flax seed. I’m very disappointed and disgusted.
